The $n$th row of Pascal's Triangle has $n+1$ numbers, so the first 20 rows have $1+2+3+\cdots+20$ numbers.  We can add up these numbers using the formula for the sum of an arithmetic series: \begin{align*}
1+2+3+\cdots+20 &= \frac{20\cdot21}{2} \\
&= 10\cdot21 \\
&= \boxed{210}.
\end{align*}
